<item>
            <title>[MATH-904] FastMath.pow deviates from Math.pow for negative, finite base values with an exponent 2^52 &lt; y &lt; 2^53 </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-904</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As reported by Jeff Hain:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;pow(double,double):&lt;br/&gt;
Math.pow(-1.0,5.000000000000001E15) = -1.0&lt;br/&gt;
FastMath.pow(-1.0,5.000000000000001E15) = 1.0&lt;br/&gt;
===&amp;gt; This is due to considering that power is an even&lt;br/&gt;
integer if it is &amp;gt;= 2^52, while you need to test&lt;br/&gt;
that it is &amp;gt;= 2^53 for it.&lt;br/&gt;
===&amp;gt; replace&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;if (y &amp;gt;= TWO_POWER_52 || y &amp;lt;= -TWO_POWER_52)&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
with&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;if (y &amp;gt;= 2*TWO_POWER_52 || y &amp;lt;= -2*TWO_POWER_52)&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
and that solves it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
